claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: A table summarizing baseline characteristics (race, sex, season, influenza case status, high-risk condition) of study participants aged 18–64 and ≥65 years by vaccine received (RIV4, SD-IIV4, HD-IIV4, Adj-IV) The table provides demographic and season distribution data by vaccine type but contains no information on antigenic matching to WHO- or FDA-selected strains, so it does not support the claim Note: Analysis limited to the displayed baseline characteristics table; no antigenic match data is present
